§ TYPE-SYSTEM THEOREMS ← §§ 03 + §§ 12

  T1 : progress (standard Wright-Felleisen)
    ∀ well-typed-term t, either t=value OR ∃ t' . t → t'
    status : ◐ (operational-semantics in §§ 03 • mechanized pending)
    discharge : stage1-Coq-proof or Lean4 port

  T2 : preservation
    ∀ well-typed t : T, t → t' ⇒ t' : T
    status : ◐
    discharge : same-as-T1

  T3 : capability-soundness (Pony-6-lineage)
    ∀ well-typed program, no data-race reachable
    ∀ iso-reference : consumed-exactly-once (linear)
    status : ◐ (Pony-paper-soundness carries + region+gen-ref extensions argued)
    discharge : stage2-Coq-extension beyond-Pony-baseline

  T4 : refinement-discharge-completeness
    ∀ well-formed refinement-obligation, SMT decides OR flags-Unknown
    status : ✓ (Z3 + CVC5 completeness for supported-theories)
    unknowns : higher-order + arbitrary-quantifier-alternation (documented)

